%% Argo Workflows - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant DSP as DSP API Server
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant WFC as workflow-controller<br/>SA: argo
    participant Pod as Workflow Pod<br/>(argoexec sidecar)
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP
    participant Client as Client (UI/CLI)
    participant Server as argo-server<br/>2746/TCP HTTPS

    Note over DSP, S3: Flow 1: Workflow Execution

    DSP->>K8s: Create Workflow CR<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8s-->>WFC: Watch notification<br/>HTTPS, SA Token
    WFC->>K8s: Create Pod(s) for steps<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token (argo)
    K8s-->>Pod: Pod scheduled & started

    Pod->>K8s: Report status<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Pod->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, Access Key
    S3-->>Pod: Upload confirmation
    Pod->>K8s: Create WorkflowTaskResult CR<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    WFC->>K8s: Update Workflow status<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    Note over Client, DB: Flow 2: API Access (via argo-server)

    Client->>Server: REST/gRPC request<br/>HTTPS/2746, Bearer Token / SSO
    Server->>K8s: Impersonated API call<br/>HTTPS/443, Impersonated SA Token
    K8s-->>Server: API response
    Server->>DB: Archive workflow (optional)<br/>TCP/5432, Username/Password
    DB-->>Server: Confirmation
    Server-->>Client: JSON/gRPC response

    Note over WFC, K8s: Flow 3: CronWorkflow Scheduling

    WFC->>WFC: Cron scheduler triggers
    WFC->>K8s: Create Workflow CR from CronWorkflow<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token (argo)
    K8s-->>WFC: Workflow CR created
